====================
simple if(statement)
====================

-> To execute the statements based on condition 

syntax
------

if(condition){

		//stmts
		//stmts
		//stmts

}

Example:
========

public class Count {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		int a = 10;
		int b = 5;

		if (a > b)
			System.out.println("true");
	}

}

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

if you want more than one line of comments output then use { }

Example
=======

public class Count {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		int a = 10;
		int b = 5;

		if (a > b){
			System.out.println("condition is ");
			System.out.println("true")
			}
	}

}


                                        ===================
                                        if-else(statement)
                                        ===================


-> if condition is not true then display the else msg..

Example
=======


public class Count {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		int age = 20;

		if (age >= 18) {

			System.out.println("eligible for vote ");
		} else {

			System.out.println("not eligible for vote ");
		}

	}

}


