3. if - else - if- else - if -else
----------------------------------

-> if condition 1 is pass then it will execute only condition 1
-> if condition 1 is failed then it will check condition 2
-> if condition 2 is pass then it will execute only condition 2
-> if condition 2 is failed then it will check condition 3
-> if condition 3 is pass then it will execute only condition 3
-> if condition 3 is failed then it will execute directly statement 4


-> if (condition_1){

        //stmts 1
 
 }else if (condition_2){
	
	//stmts 2

 }else if (condition_3){

      //stmts 3
}else{
 
       //stmts 4

    }





Example
========

public class Count {

	public static void main(String[] args) {

		int a = 15;
		
		if(a > 0) {
			System.out.println("a is positive number");
		}else if(a < 0 ) {
			
			System.out.println("a is negative number ");
		}else {
			
			System.out.println("a is zero");
		}

	}

}








